<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880805-0168 </DOCNO><HL> Meridian National Project </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MRCO </CO><DATELINE> TOLEDO, Ohio  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Meridian National Corp. said Michigan officials gave it a permit to construct a hazardous liquid waste storage and treatment facility in Detroit.    Construction is expected to begin this year and to take about one year to complete. The steel-treatment and waste disposal and management concern said the cost of the facility, including the cost of obtaining the permit, will be $5.5 million. </TEXT></DOC>